    {
      "id": "edge-port-policy",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "3. Port Policy",
      "position": {
        "x": 640,
        "y": 360
      },
      "width": 440,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Port Policy (REQUIRED)\n\n- `sourcePort` and `targetPort` may be omitted\n- omitted ports are interpreted as the default **root** port\n- if ports are provided, they MUST exist on the node\n- tools and agents MUST NOT invent non-existent ports\n\nThe canonical portable meaning is therefore: omitted == `root`, explicit non-root ports must validate.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
            "key": "markdown",
            "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
            "source": "local",
            "version": ">=0.1.0"
          },
          "views": [
            {
              "key": "markdown",
