    {
      "id": "edge-types",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "4. Edge Type Contract",
      "position": {
        "x": -720,
        "y": 760
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Edge Type Contract (OPTIONAL)\n\n`type` MAY be provided as a string runtime render primitive.\n\nIt controls how the edge is drawn or routed, not the full semantic contract by itself.\n\nExamples currently in use include:\n- `reference`\n- `relates`\n- `default`\n- `straight`\n- `governs`\n\nMoving forward:\n- a plain edge remains valid without a class or type\n- if `type` is omitted, the renderer falls back to a simple line\n- when an edge class is assigned, the class may provide `defaultEdgeType`\n- an instance-level `type` override wins when both are present\n\nProjects may still use additional string types, but durable relationship meaning should live in the edge class when reusable semantics are intended.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
            "key": "markdown",
            "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
            "source": "local",
            "version": ">=0.1.0"
          },
          "views": [
            {
              "key": "markdown",
              "intent": "editor",
